# =============================================================================
# .pii-rules.local — TEMPLATE
#
# Copy this file to `.pii-rules.local` (gitignored) and add patterns specific
# to your commits: client names, family names, internal codenames, anything
# that must NEVER enter a public commit.
#
# Format: one regex per non-blank, non-comment line. Same engine as
# .githooks/pii-rules-generic.txt. Lines beginning with `#` are comments.
#
# YAML-style category headers (commented out below) are PURELY for human
# organization — the scanner ignores them. They're here so you can group
# patterns when the file grows.
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# client_names:
#   Add client / company names here. Use word boundaries (\b) where you want
#   to avoid matching substrings.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Example:
# \bClientCo\b
# \bAnotherCompany\b

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# personal_names:
#   Family members, roommates, partners, collaborators by handle.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Example:
# \bFirstName Lastname\b
# \bNickname\b

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# internal_codenames:
#   Project codenames you don't want public, internal product names, etc.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Example:
# \bProjectAlbatross\b

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# personal_handles:
#   Discord handles, IRC nicks, gamer tags. (Email is already in the generic
#   ruleset; these are platform-specific identifiers.)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Example:
# @your_handle\b
